TITLE: Calling Firebase Functions with Combine (With Parameters)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to call a Firebase Function named 'helloWorld' with a parameter using Combine. It handles the completion and receives the function result.
SOURCE: https://github.com/firebase/firebase-ios-sdk/blob/main/FirebaseCombineSwift/README.md#2025-04-11_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
let helloWorld = Functions.functions().httpsCallable("helloWorld")
helloWorld.call("Peter")
  .sink { completion in
    switch completion {
      case .finished:
        print("Finished")
      case let .failure(error):
        print("\(error.localizedDescription)")
    }
  } receiveValue: { functionResult in
    if let result = functionResult.data as? String {
      print("The function returned: \(result)")
    }
  }
  .store(in: &cancellables)
```

