TITLE: Handling Incoming Dynamic Links for Passwordless Authentication in iOS
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of the SceneDelegate function that handles incoming dynamic links for email link/passwordless authentication. The function verifies if the incoming URL is a Firebase Auth sign-in link, saves it to UserDefaults, and posts a notification to continue the authentication process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/firebase/firebase-ios-sdk/blob/main/FirebaseAuth/Tests/SampleSwift/README.md#2025-04-11_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
// SceneDelegate.swift

private func handleIncomingDynamicLink(_ incomingURL: URL) {

    let link = incomingURL.absoluteString

    // Here, we check if our dynamic link is a sign-link (the one we emailed our user!)
    if Auth.auth().isSignIn(withEmailLink: link) {

        // Save the link as it will be used in the next step to complete login
        UserDefaults.standard.set(link, forKey: "Link")

        // Post a notification to the PasswordlessViewController to resume authentication
        NotificationCenter.default.post(Notification(name: Notification.Name("PasswordlessEmailNotificationSuccess")))
    }
}
```

