TITLE: Avoiding Deadlocks in Firebase Auth with Internal Method Pattern
DESCRIPTION: Pattern for implementing public synchronous methods that need to be callable from both public and private contexts. This approach prevents deadlocks that would occur when calling dispatch_sync from within the same queue by creating an internal implementation that doesn't use dispatch_sync.
SOURCE: https://github.com/firebase/firebase-ios-sdk/blob/main/FirebaseAuth/Docs/threading.md#2025-04-11_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: objectivec
CODE:
```
- (ReturnType)somethingInternal {
  // Compute result.
  return computedResult;
}

- (ReturnType)something {
  __block ReturnType result;
  dispatch_sync(FIRAuthGlobalWorkQueue(), ^{
    result = [self somethingInternal];
  });
  return result;
}
```

