TITLE: Platform-Specific Source Selection for Firestore Util Library in CMake
DESCRIPTION: Selects the appropriate source files for the firestore_util library based on the target platform (Apple, Windows, or Linux/UNIX). This ensures platform-specific implementations are used while excluding incompatible source files.
SOURCE: https://github.com/firebase/firebase-ios-sdk/blob/main/Firestore/core/CMakeLists.txt#2025-04-11_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: cmake
CODE:
```
file(
  GLOB util_sources
  src/util/*.cc
  src/util/*.h
)

if(APPLE)
  firebase_ios_glob(
    util_sources APPEND src/util/*.mm
    EXCLUDE src/util/*_win.cc
  )

elseif(WIN32)
  firebase_ios_glob(
    util_sources EXCLUDE
    src/util/*_apple.*
    src/util/*_posix.*
  )

else()
  # Linux and other UNIX systems.
  firebase_ios_glob(
    util_sources EXCLUDE
    src/util/*_apple.cc
    src/util/*_win.cc
  )
endif()
```

